Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the sweet potato. Peel the @sweet potato{1} and chop into roughly 2cm cubes. Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (little trees!). Crush the @black peppercorns{1/2} in a #pestle and mortar{}. 

> TIP: If you don't have a pestle and mortar you can put them in a freezer bag and whack them with a rolling pin!

Cook the sweet potato in your pan of boiling water until soft, ~{15-20%minutes}. Next, add the broccoli to a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a splash of oil, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of pepper. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, sandwich the @British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of #clingfilm{}. Bash the chicken with a #rolling pin{} or the base of a saucepan until each breast is just under 1cm thick.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the chicken with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{}. Once hot, lay the chicken in the pan and fry until cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side. The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, transfer to another baking tray and keep it warm in the oven.

> TIP: Don't wash your pan as we'll use it to make the sauce tastier later.

When the sweet potato is soft, reserve some of the sweet potato cooking water (@water{100%ml}), then drain the sweet potato in a #colander{} and pop it back in the pan. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, then stir in a knob of @butter{1%knob}(if you have some), along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== Peppercorn Sauce ==

Put your now empty frying pan on medium-high heat. Add the reserved water. Stir in the @chicken stock powder{1/2} and crushed peppercorns. Simmer until reduced by half, ~{5%minutes}, stirring to get the yummy bits from the bottom of the pan. Take off the heat and mix in the @soured cream{75%g}.

== To Serve ==

Slice the chicken and serve with the roasted broccoli, sweet potato mash and a drizzle of peppercorn sauce. Enjoy!